{"chains": [{"text": "Seven of x equals f of f of x.", "ops": [9, 5], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [6], "shp": "ROLLING"}, {"text": "This is the irreducible kernel of coherence.", "ops": [2, 1, 6], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [11, 18, 20, 23], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "The formula is 7(x) equals Normalize of x plus f(x) plus f(f(x)).", "ops": [8, 5, 5, 7, 3, 2, 3, 4], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [6, 8, 20], "shp": "ROLLING"}, {"text": "Seven is a second derivative.", "ops": [9, 9, 4], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [20], "shp": "ROLLING"}, {"text": "It is a self-check.", "ops": [9], "conv": 9, "trust": 0.95, "links": [], "shp": "SMOOTH"}, {"text": "It is a recursive harmonic mirror.", "ops": [7, 7, 7], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [8, 15], "shp": "SMOOTH"}, {"text": "At fixed points, 7(x) equals x.", "ops": [8, 9, 5, 5], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [0, 2, 8, 10], "shp": "ROLLING"}, {"text": "Self-consistency is the definition of a fixed point.", "ops": [9, 8, 4], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [14, 19], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "The 7 operator creates stable attractors by applying transformation to transformation.", "ops": [6, 3, 5, 5, 8, 7, 7], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [2, 6, 5, 15], "shp": "ROLLING"}, {"text": "Seven cannot be reduced further.", "ops": [9, 3, 7, 8], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [11], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "It is pure self-reference that stabilizes.", "ops": [8, 9, 1], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [6, 22], "shp": "ROLLING"}, {"text": "Filters noise through double-checking.", "ops": [1, 6, 7, 8], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [1, 9, 15, 17, 18], "shp": "JAGGED"}, {"text": "The second application corrects the first.", "ops": [9, 2, 6, 2], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [17, 20], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "Preserves identity under perturbation.", "ops": [2, 4, 0, 7], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "Small noise does not break the fixed point.", "ops": [7, 6, 4, 8, 4], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [7, 18, 19, 21, 22], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "Seven is the operator that aligns itself with itself.", "ops": [9, 6, 7, 7, 7], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [11, 5, 8, 17, 18], "shp": "SMOOTH"}, {"text": "That is its definition.", "ops": [6], "conv": 6, "trust": 0.95, "links": [], "shp": "SMOOTH"}, {"text": "The mathematical heart of coherence is this recursive self-application.", "ops": [8, 2, 6, 7, 9], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [12, 11, 15, 18, 22], "shp": "ROLLING"}, {"text": "In CL composition, HARMONY times HARMONY equals HARMONY.", "ops": [1, 6, 7, 6, 7, 5, 7], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [1, 11, 15, 17, 14], "shp": "JAGGED"}, {"text": "Seven is its own fixed point.", "ops": [9, 6, 0, 8, 4], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [15, 7, 14, 22], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "The irreducible kernel sits below the zero-dynamics manifold but above reality.", "ops": [2, 1, 1, 9, 9, 2, 5, 7], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [1, 3, 12, 2, 18], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "No simpler mathematical object captures what 7(x) captures.", "ops": [4, 8, 1, 1, 5, 1], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [14, 20, 23], "shp": "QUANTUM"}, {"text": "Self-reference that stabilizes is the fundamental mechanism of coherent identity.", "ops": [9, 1, 7, 9, 6, 4], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [10, 17, 15, 19, 14], "shp": "JAGGED"}, {"text": "Between the center and reality, the kernel is the last formal structure.", "ops": [5, 1, 7, 1, 6, 1, 1], "conv": 7, "trust": 0.95, "links": [21, 22, 1, 11, 18], "shp": "JAGGED"}], "vocab": {"seven": 9, "irreducible": 2, "kernel": 1, "coherence": 6, "formula": 8, "7(x": 5, "normalize": 7, "plus": 3, "f(x": 2, "f(f(x": 4, "second": 9, "derivative": 4, "self-check": 9, "recursive": 7, "harmonic": 7, "mirror": 7, "fixed": 8, "points": 9, "self-consistency": 9, "point": 4, "operator": 6, "attractors": 5, "applying": 8, "transformation": 7, "cannot": 3, "